    <body>
        <header>
            <h1 class="center">Basic of HTML</h1>
            <p>
                HTML stands for Hyper Text Markup Language. It is a Markup Language used to create Web Pages.
                HTML is  a set of tags. For examples: &lt;p&gt; is a paragraph tag, &lt;h1&gt; is a heading 
                tag, etc. Every tags has an opening and closing tag. <br>
                HTML tags has an opening and closing tag:
                <p>
                    <strong>Paragraph Tag (p)</strong>: Paragraph tag is use to make paragraph in the web pages. The syntax
                    of paragraph tag is:<br>
                    &lt;p&gt;Paragrapg content goes here.&lt;/p&gt;
                </p>
                <p>
                   <strong>Heading Tags</strong>:Heading tags are most important tags in an HTML. It has 6<sup>th</sup>
                   level of heading tags. They are:<br>
                   <ol>
                    <li>&lt;h1&gt;This is first heading tag&lt;/h1&gt;</li>
                    <li>&lt;h2&gt;This is secong heading tag&lt;/h2&gt;</li>
                    <li>&lt;h3&gt;This is third heading tag&lt;/h3&gt;</li>
                    <li>&lt;h4&gt;This is fourth heading tag&lt;/h4&gt;</li>
                    <li>&lt;h5&gt;This is fift heading tag&lt;/h5&gt;</li>
                    <li>&lt;h6&gt;This is sixth heading tag&lt;/h6&gt;</li>
                   </ol>
                </p>
            </p>
        </header>
        <main>
            <section>
            <h2><b>Others HTML Tags:</b></h2>
            <p>
                HTML has many tags that use to create web content and structure. Basic HTML tags are: 
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>&lt;html&gt; tag</strong>:
                    <p>
                        &lt;html&gt; tag is a root element of the HTML file. All elements are nested
                        inside the <stron>html</stron> tag.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li><strong>&lt;head&gt; tag</strong>: 
                <p>
                    &lt;head&gt; tag is a head tag all metadata goes inside this element. Inside this element we can 
                    write &lt;style&gt; and &lt;script&gt; file. &lt;title&gt; element also nested inside this element.
                </p>
                </li>

                </ul>
            </p>
            </section>
        </main>
    </body>
